args: When you work together, your power\ngoes beyond the limits of what any\nsingle person can do.
I am willing to risk my life for the\nsake of my pride as an engineer.
(There are other fine artisans besides me\ngranda, and each has their own path.)
(I was walkin' the path you taught me.\nGoin' it alone.)
(There's more than just me physical\nstrength that need reinforcin'.\nI know that now.)
If I find what that is, I bet I could make\nthis sword here better, too...
(So once I find me own path,\nthe Golden Anvil will be mine!)
The sponsor of the tournament is\ngoing to explain. Come on!
What's the meaning of this, guildmaster?\nWhy aren't we holding the Golden Anvil?
There have been increasing incidents\nof Empire soldiers kidnapping both\nengineers and blacksmiths of late.
An Empire solider said they were\nforcin' smiths to make weapons\noff in some secret location.
And you think the Empire\nmight come here?
I do. After all, if it's smiths they've want,\nwe have the best in the world huddled\ntogether under a single roof.
The location of the Golden Anvil is\nno secret, so we have to assume the\nEmpire is already on its way.
My first and greatest responsibility is to\nprotect the participants, which is why we\nare canceling this year's tournament.
Aw, hellfire! I spent all year\ntraining for this moment!
Damn the Empire! This is just another in a\nlong list of things they've stolen from us!
Nay. We won't let 'em do it.
I'm still tryin' to put what I\nmean to say into words...
Every artisan walks a different path.\nWhat's important to one can be\nless important to another.
But we all want the same thing in the end:\nTo be the best we can be.
Which is why all those different paths\nmeet up here at the Golden Anvil.
That's right! And we won't let the Empire\nor anyone else take it from us!
The tournament is worth the risk!
I won't let the Empire crush my dream!
Your dreams and pride will mean nothing\nif you fall into the hands of the Empire.
Which is why we won't let it happen.
To think you would all risk your lives\nfor the glory of smithing... *sniff*
So be it. The tournament will proceed...\nbut on one condition!
We are going to change the location.
You mean, like, to a place where\nthe Empire isn't going to show up?
Oh, I've a much more active\nsort of plan in mind...
We'll show the Empire exactly what\nhappens when you mess with us!
